snippet.textDisplay:
I am surprised nobody is mentioning that
1. LeBron has picked the best player available on every single pick he has made, maybe Kawhi should have been picked before AD. Any other selection clearly has been the best.
2. The starting 5 is exactly EAST vs WEST. After the starters had been picked, I was thinking LeBron and Giannis could have arranged to make it an Eastern vs Western Allstars game. I was wrong there. Giannis picked the guys he likes most and LeBron continued to choose the best available. Most interesting moment this year was the reveiled opinion about James Harden. I didn't expect them to be that honest or open in public.
